he dark hub matches other ERP surfaces on tablets (cards already use `--color-hub-border` — no bare `--line` swap needed).\par 130. Hub workspace strip tablet chrome (`erp-master-spec-2026.css`, Rules 0 + 1 + 2): Inside the existing ≤900px satellite block, `body.hub-page .board-nav-inner` horizontal padding 12px → 8px; `body.hub-page .board-nav-trigger` padding 11px 16px → 10px 12px so the sticky strip aligns with tightened `.erp-connection-strip` padding on the hub.\par 131. Maintenance surfaces off legacy `--panel` (`app-theme.css`, Rules 0 + 12): `body.erp-maintenance` `.subtab` (default pill), `.shop-col` (shop board column shell), and `.sidebar-expand-fab` `background` → `var(--color-bg-card, var(--panel))` so `design-tokens` can steer card white without a broad `--panel` migration.\par 132. Maintenance default chrome + section cards (`app-theme.css`, Rules 0 + 12): `body.erp-maintenance` generic `.btn` / `button` (excluded specialty controls unchanged) and `input|select|textarea` `background` → `var(--color-bg-card, var(--panel))`; `.maint-section-card` gradient end stop `var(--panel)` → `var(--color-bg-card, var(--panel))`.\par 133. Fuel + banking satellite page/panel fills (`app-theme.css`, Rules 0 + 1): `body.dispatch-page` / `body.fuel-board` shared font rule split: dispatch keeps `background: var(--bg)`; fuel uses `var(--color-bg-page, var(--bg))`. `.banking-page .panel` and `body.fuel-board .panel` gradient lower stop `var(--panel)` → `var(--color-bg-card, var(--panel))`.\par 1. Priorities: Which rules are mandatory for the next release vs nice-to-have (spec asks for everything at once; engineering may still sequence).\par 2. Rule 10 / React path: Shared component + build step vs one canonical HTML/JS cost-line implementation.\par 3. Rule 4 — + New menu: Which rows are deep-links vs new modals (avoid new save APIs unless explicitly scoped).\par 4. Rule 18: Thin `GET /api/qbo/accounts`-style aliases vs documenting existing catalog routes only.\par 5. Regr